Family Bank of Kenya Full-Year Profit Jumps as Income From Loans Increases

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-29T04:03:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/family-bank-of-kenya-full-year-profit-jumps-as-income-from-loans-increases.html
Family Bank Ltd., a Kenyan lender
that plans to list on the  Nairobi Stock Exchange , said full-year
profit surged 77 percent as earnings from loans increased.  Net income jumped to 391 million shillings ($4.65 million)
in the 12 months through December, from 220.9 million shillings
a year earlier, the Nairobi-based lender said in a statement
published in the Daily Nation newspaper today. Net interest
income, the money banks earn from interest charges on loans,
climbed 42 percent to 1.67 billion shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  